      "description": "Available for acquisition is an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Laguna Seca Blue. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp ZF 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable differential lock. This vehicle has undergone rigorous preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement with structural plates. The suspension utilizes original geometry with refreshed bushings for precise turn-in, while the factory-spec cross-drilled rotors provide exceptional thermal management. Cosmetically, the finish exhibits original paint depth with no evidence of road rash or oxidation. This is an uncompromising, turn-key example for the purist collector.",
